This paper deals with decoding low-density parity check (LDPC) codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It also involves communication networks (cs.NI) since the LDPC codes are used in communication systems. The paper proposes a new algorithm for decoding LDPC codes, which involves optimization techniques (cs.SY) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves analyzing the performance of the algorithm, which can be considered as a data analysis problem (cs.DS).
